I'm not entirely sure why, but it feels like in terms of stories /hmofa/'s taste stopped evolving about two or three years ago. For a while now it seems that for anything to gain traction it needs to fit a few specific criteria or be banished to the bottom of the masterbin. First, little to no sexual content. Second, there needs to be kind of 'will they won't they' teasing added to the plot. And third, it needs to be posted chapter by chapter, usually over a long period of time.

I'm not saying these are the most popular stories by any specific metric, but when I think of stories that get lots of recommendations and discussion within the thread these are just the ones that pop in my mind first.

>TLoF
>HATS
>Deer to my Heart
>Vice Versa
>Rood awakening

And what do these all have in common? Either none or a small amount of NSFW content, some kind of romantic tension, and they were all posted piecemeal over months/years. What does this all mean? I don't fucking know, but generally speaking stagnation doesn't do most communities any good in the long run, especially communities centered around an inherently creative topic like /hmofa/.
